    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-12T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-12T15:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GGW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guthrie</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Chargé d’Affaires in China</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-12T15:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Ascertain and report as to truth of statements made in English press that
                    Japanese Government proposes to extend war to regions east of Hwang-ho River and
                    expel all Germans not only from Dalny but from Mukden, Changchun, and even
                    Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
